    "department": "Software",
    "description": "About Sesame\n\nSesame believes in a future where computers are lifelike - with the ability to see, hear, and collaborate with us in ways that feel natural and human. With this vision, we're designing a new kind of computer, focused on making voice agents part of our daily lives. Our team brings together founders from Oculus and Ubiquity6, alongside proven leaders from Meta, Google, and Apple, with deep expertise spanning hardware and software. Join us in shaping a future where computers truly come alive.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nWe're looking for a hands-on QA Manager to build and lead our quality assurance function from the ground up. You'll personally advocate for quality while establishing testing processes that ensure Sesame products meet the highest standards. You'll work at the intersection of hardware, software, and user experience, creating technology that feels truly alive.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n - Lead quality and testing of hardware and software to deliver outstanding customer experiences.\n\n - Develop and execute test plans, test cases, and testing frameworks that cover the full stack.\n\n - Create opportunities for automated test coverage.\n\n - Partner with engineering, product, and design teams to integrate quality considerations from concept through production.\n\n - Identify, document, and advocate for critical issues through hands-on testing and cross-team collaboration.\n\n - Help triage bugs and work with teams to prioritize fixes based on severity, user impact, and release timelines.\n\n - Build processes that balance speed with quality in a fast-paced startup environment.\n\n - Grow and mentor a team of QA testers with a culture rooted in delivering quality.\n\nRequired Qualifications:\n\n - 5+ years in QA with at least 2 years in a lead or management role.\n\n - Strong understanding of consumer QA testing best practices.\n\n - Experience with test management tools (JIRA, TestRail, or similar).\n\n - Proven ability to build testing processes from scratch while remaining deeply involved in hands-on testing.\n\n - Track record of balancing management responsibilities with personal testing work to ship quality products on time.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\n - Experience in testing consumer hardware.\n\n - Experience in testing consumer software.\n\n - Experience with QA automation and/or engineering.\n\n - Experience building new testing systems and tools.\n\n - Experience working with QA vendors.\n\n - Experience with regulatory compliance and safety standards for consumer electronics.\n\n - Experience launching new products into mobile app stores.\n\nSesame is committed to a workplace where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered. We welcome all qualified applicants, embracing diversity in race, gender, identity, orientation, ability, and more. We provide reasonable accommodations for applicants with disabilities. Contact careers@sesame.com for assistance.\n\nFull-time Employee Benefits: \n\n - 401 (k) max employer match: 3.5% of compensation\n\n - 100% employer-paid health, vision, and dental benefits for you and your dependents\n\n - Unlimited PTO and sick time\n\n - Flexible spending account with employer matching up to $1,650/year (medical FSA)\n\n - Guardian Employee Assistance Program (EAP)\n\n - Opportunity to share in the company's success with competitive stock options\n\nBenefits do not apply to contingent/contract workers.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
